ReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Another parchment distribution question</span><hr size=1> Imagine the following: You have a good group, and fight for some hours in PoP. Parchments do drop, of course not often but steadily. Your luck with the dice just isnt that great today, and so you are one of the last to have no parchment.<br>
<br>
Then the only other person who has none yet has to leave (shaman) and your group gets a replacement (chanter). Sure enough, another parchment drops within five mins of the chanter being in group, and he claims to roll on it.<br>
<br>
Happened last night to me. Luckily I won the roll. I should add that I had announced a bit ago that I would have to leave group soon also, so I thought that this parchment should have been defaulted to me with no question.<br>
<br>
What do you think? Was this greedy of me to expect some return for some hours invested? Or should every person in the group have the same rights to rolling, regardless how long they were in the group?<br>
<br>
Izudin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 12:18:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Another parchment distribution question</span><hr size=1> A drop happens when it happens and unless you have made a special rule the roll should be made with the people precent and for decency items like parchments should only be awarded to people who didn't have a drop yet. It does make it complicated if you have been in a group for a long time with people rotating in and out and could be solved by saying something like:&quot;I did get a drop XX hours ago, but would like to start rolling again&quot;<br>
<br>
nmee <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kalamos>Kalamos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 448<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 5:11:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Another parchment distribution question</span><hr size=1> If I join a group that's been going for awhile, and a parchment drops soon thereafter, I always ask which casters haven't gotten a parchment.  If any casters have been in the group awhile and not gotten one yet, I always sit out of the roll.<br>
<br>
Set the rules ahead of time.  That way there's no confusion or hurt feelings.<br>
<br>
