<br>
If a caster enters a group with 3 other casters, he should expect no greater than 1 in 4 odds of getting the next parchment drop.  If you were the one caster of the original 3 who hadn't gotten one yet, you would obviously get the 3 in 4 odds of the drop.  Of course, try explaining that to a group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zacatac>Zacatac</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1474<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 10:52:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Another parchment distribution question</span><hr size=1> A shaman friend of mine had a good story.<br>
<br>
Pick-group camping CT for the Boots of Flowing Slime.  Boots drop, the cleric in group wins the roll.  Couple hours later, some people have to leave.  Group evacs, half the group leaves, 3 more join.  They go back down to the camp.<br>
<br>
New group has same cleric, enchanter and shaman.  Boots drop, and again the cleric wins the roll !  Boots are not LORE, so cleric gets both for the night.  And since he considers it a &quot;new group&quot; and all rolls start over, he happily took them.<br>
<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hexxis00>Hexxis00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 50<br> <font color=#333333>(12/3/02 11:17:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1691.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/dc/dbvortex/Vortexgifanimations/PiccoloBeamCannon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Another parchment distribution question</span><hr size=1> There is a chance I would never have grouped with that cleric again after that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Certain amout of greed isn't tolerated well by me.<br>
In any case the original question was are you beeing greedy for being the last caster in the group that didn't have a parchment and not wanting the chanter in the group roll on it.<br>
I don't think so, however when I am group leader I always do things a certain way when parchments have dropped.<br>
I always make sure that everyone on the first few get an oppertunity to roll and win,.. but when there are 1 or 2 ppl left that still need and a caster that has a parchment has a parchment has left the group I always tell the replacement that xxx and xxx are up b4 he/she is cause we been here xxx hours and they have yet to get one. Usually that isn't a problem...... I have had no complaints yet so.... give thata try.<br>
<br>
